text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!PhonologicalPhenomenaInSpokenLanguages]]%0a%0a!German final-obstruent devoicing%0a%0a:Author: xiranw%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aIn German, voiced obstruents become voiceless in syllable-final position.%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIn German (Indo-European), voiced obstruents become voiceless in syllable-final position. Below are 3 examples of this phonological process:%0a%0a1. [hʊndə] (dogs), [hʊnt] (dog). Notice how [d] is devoiced and becomes [t] in [hʊnt].%0a%0a2. [bɛʁɡə] (mountains), [bɛrk] (mountain). Notice how [g] is devoiced and becomes [k] in [bɛrk].%0a%0a3. [biːɡən] (to bend), [biːk.zaːm] (flexible). Notice how [g] is devoiced and becomes [k] in [biːk.zaːm].%0a%0aLooking at the first two examples may lead one to conclude that this devoicing only occurs in word-final position, but the third example shows that the process is in fact more broad: it applies in syllable-final position. %0a%0aThis devoicing process is natural because during a syllable break, the vocal folds are abducted / not vibrating. The devoicing of obstruents in syllable-final position means the abduction of the vocal folds is happening sooner. Take [biːk.zaːm], for example. Rather than starting to abduct the vocal folds at the syllable break, the vocal folds become abducted at the production of the [k], then stay abducted throughout [k] and during the syllable break.%0a%0aSources: https://www.researchgate.net/publication/2315640_Voicing_and_devoicing_in_English_German_and_Dutch_evidence_for_domain-specific_identity_constraints%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: B:)%0a(:Category: PhonologicalPhenomenaInSpokenLanguages:)
